To maintain and develop positive business relationships with a customer's key personnel involved in or directly relevant to a logistics activity:

1. Establish regular communication channels
2. Provide consistent, high-quality service
3. Be responsive to customer needs and concerns
4. Offer personalized solutions
5. Demonstrate industry expertise
6. Be proactive in problem-solving
7. Schedule periodic face-to-face meetings
8. Show appreciation for their business
9. Keep them informed of new services or improvements
10. Seek feedback and act on it
11. Maintain professionalism at all times
12. Be transparent about processes and potential issues
13. Offer value-added services when possible
14. Remember and acknowledge important dates or milestones
15. Cultivate a long-term partnership mindset
</OUTPUT_TEXT>
